definition.value: A glucosyl group obtained by removing the hydroxy group from the hemiacetal function of D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucose.
An L-alpha-amino acid; the L-isomer of lysine.
A monocarboxylic acid anion resuting from selective deprotonation of the carboxy group of phosphoenolpyruvic acid.
A pseudohalide anion obtained by deprotonation of the thiol group of thiocyanic acid.
